        <div type="letter">
            <div type="text">
                <opener>
                    <placeName><hi rend="print">Down, | Beckenham, Kent.</hi></placeName>
                    <date>July 15, ’73</date>
                    <salute>Gentlemen,</salute>
                </opener>
                <div type="transcription">
                     
<p>I am very much obliged to you for having sent me your three essays.<ref target="#foot.f1"/> Although the subject is beyond my scope, nevertheless your investigations seem to me the most important &amp; interesting of any which I have read for a very long time.</p>
<p>With my sincere respect &amp; hopes for your continued success | I remain Gentlemen | Yours very faithfully | Charles Darwin</p> 
                </div>
            </div>

            
            
            
            
            
            
        </div>
        
        
        <div type="footnotes">
            <note xml:id="foot.f1">Dewar and M‘Kendrick had published a three-part paper on the physiological action of light (<ref target="../bibliographies/bibl_9931.xml">Dewar and M‘Kendrick 1873</ref>).</note>
        </div>
    
